ECM Real Estate Proposes Plan to Repay Part of Debt, CTK Says

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-07-11T11:40:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/ecm-real-estate-proposes-plan-to-repay-part-of-debt-ctk-says.html
ECM Real Estate Investments AG (ECM) , an
insolvent developer, proposed a restructuring plan that would
allow repaying 48 percent of its debt to unsecured creditors,
 CTK  reported, citing an insolvency registry.  ECM would have to finish five development projects in the
 Czech Republic  and  Poland  to be able to repay the proposed
amount, the newswire said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  